**Important Links of Docker. 

Before you begin 
   -- Enable that your Machine is enabled with VT-x or AMD-v Virtualization in the BIOS. 
   -- Hypervisor 
        MAC OS --> VirtualBox , VMware Fusion or HyperKit. 
        Linux --> VirtualBox or KVM. 
        Windows --> Hyper V or virtual Box. 
        Link to Oracle VM Virtual Box --> https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads 

Incase of any questions, Please create a ticket at support@edureka.co or call the help line to create an SR. 


1. Configure a VM. 
    https://www.osboxes.org/ubuntu/
    Xeinal 16.04 --> https://sourceforge.net/projects/osboxes/files/v/vb/55-U-u/16.04/16.04.5/1604564.7z/download

    -- Prereq script. 
    #Commands 
	sudo rm /var/lib/dpkg/lock
	sudo dpkg --configure -a
	sudo rm /var/lib/apt/lists/lock
	sudo rm /var/cache/apt/archives/lock

	sudo apt-get update
	sudo apt update

	apt-get install net-tools
	apt-get install ssh
	apt-get install 

2. Docker Installation 
    Link for Linux-ubuntu --> https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/
    Link for Windows --> https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-windows/install/
    Doocker toolbox for both windows and mac --> https://docs.docker.com/toolbox/toolbox_install_mac/ 

    apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install \
    apt-transport-https \
    ca-certificates \
    curl \
    gnupg-agent \
    software-properties-common
    apt-get install docker.io 

    curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo apt-key add -
    sudo apt-key fingerprint 0EBFCD88
    sudo add-apt-repository \
   "deb [arch=amd64] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
   $(lsb_release -cs) \
   stable"

   sudo apt-get update
   sudo apt-get install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io


**install specific versio of docker --> "sudo apt-get install docker-ce=<VERSION_STRING> docker-ce-cli=<VERSION_STRING> containerd.io"

    docker -version 
    docker run hello-world 
    docker run docker/whalesay cowsay boo
    
